cs.CR, cs.LG, cs.CV, cs.AI, cs.DS 

The paper discusses a cryptanalytic attack on neural networks, which falls under the category of computer security (cs.CR). The attack specifically targets machine learning models, which suggests that it could also be classified under machine learning (cs.LG). Additionally, the paper evaluates the attack on neural networks used for image recognition (cs.CV), and the attack relies on the structure of ReLU neural networks (cs.AI). Finally, the paper involves querying the neural network to extract information, which could be considered a data structures and algorithms problem (cs.DS).
